# Alert

`TxAlert` renders an inline `role="alert"` banner with semantic color, optional leading icon, title/body slots, and an optional close button.

Reviewed against `packages/tuffex/packages/components/src/alert/src/types.ts`, `TxAlert.vue`, and `alert.test.ts`.

## Basic Usage

### Alert Variants

:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="AlertAlertVariantsDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <template>
    <div class="tuff-demo-stack">
      <TxAlert title="Heads up" message="Check your configuration." type="info" />
      <TxAlert title="Success" message="Saved successfully." type="success" />
      <TxAlert title="Warning" message="Something needs your attention." type="warning" />
      <TxAlert title="Error" message="Save failed." type="error" />
    </div>
  </template>
---
:::

## Composition Examples

### Persistent Notice

Use `closable=false` when the message is part of the page state and should not disappear locally.

```vue
<template>
  <TxAlert
    type="warning"
    title="Manual review required"
    message="This release contains unsigned artifacts."
    :closable="false"
  />
</template>
```

### Rich Title and Body

```vue
<template>
  <TxAlert type="success" @close="dismissed = true">
    <template #title>
      Runtime evidence collected
    </template>

    <p>
      Preview checks passed. Open the evidence panel for screenshots and traces.
    </p>
  </TxAlert>
</template>
```

### Text-only Banner

```vue
<template>
  <TxAlert :show-icon="false" message="Local-only demo data is shown on this page." />
</template>
```

## Interaction Contract

- The root renders `role="alert"` and a type class (`tx-alert--info`, `--success`, `--warning`, or `--error`).
- `type` selects the leading icon name: `info`, `check-circle`, `alert-triangle`, or `x-circle`.
- `showIcon=false` removes the leading icon container.
- The title row renders only when `title` or the `title` slot is present.
- The default slot replaces `message` inside `.tx-alert__message`.
- `closable=true` renders the close button, adds `tx-alert--closable`, and reserves right padding.
- Clicking the close button emits `close`; the component does not hide itself automatically.
- Close button text is icon-only and uses `aria-label="Close"`.

## API

### Props

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|-------------|
| `type` | `'info' \| 'success' \| 'warning' \| 'error'` | `'info'` | Visual intent and default icon mapping. |
| `title` | `string` | - | Optional title text. Hidden when absent and no `title` slot is provided. |
| `message` | `string` | - | Body message used when no default slot is provided. |
| `closable` | `boolean` | `true` | Render the close button and close padding. |
| `showIcon` | `boolean` | `true` | Render the semantic leading icon. |

### Events

| Event | Payload | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `close` | - | Emitted when the close button is clicked. |

### Slots

| Slot | Props | Description |
|------|------|-------------|
| `title` | - | Custom title content. |
| `default` | - | Custom body content. Replaces `message`. |

## Best Practices

- Use alerts for contextual page feedback, not as a toast replacement.
- Keep `type` aligned with the user impact: `error` for failed actions, `warning` for risk, `info` for neutral guidance.
- Handle `close` in the host by removing the alert or persisting dismissal state.
- Use `closable=false` for compliance, blocking, or always-relevant notices.
- Do not put primary workflows inside the alert body; place action buttons after the alert where layout and semantics are clearer.


## Review Notes

- Reviewed against `packages/tuffex/packages/components/src/alert/src/TxAlert.vue`, `types.ts`, and `alert.test.ts`.
- **Verified coverage:** `alert.test.ts` covers semantic alert role, type class, title/message rendering, icon visibility, title/default slots, closable hiding, and `close` emit behavior.
- Accessibility note: `role="alert"` announces content assertively. Use short, actionable copy and avoid mounting multiple new alerts at once.

